          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Babar Akhtar"
          },
          "datePublished": "2023-08-02",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "My child studies in this school from pre primary to class x passed out in 2020. It had class room with two fan for 40 student  and desk for the student was too small & classes have no proper ventilation (with only 2 fans for 40 student) as I found out during my orientation for new classes. Student are discourage to opt particular stream(science) even if student have good marks and offered humanities stream. Science stream for class xi is offered to the student of other school so that they can get  maximum admission charges. As I think my experience with school for 13(Thirteen) years was not encouraging.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Shri Shikshayatan School - Hazra Road"
          },
          "author": {
